Series I: Books

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series contains notes, research, drafts and reviews related to the books Judt authored throughout his career.

The bulk of the material in this series is from Postwar. There are also notes and research related to Past Imperfect, A Grand Illusion?, and Burden of Responsibility. Judt's papers contained drafts of essay collections he titled "Israel Book," "State of Exception" and "Essays." All of these appear to be alternative titles for Reappraisals.

The subseries also contain reviews and correspondence related to each of Judt's works. Correspondence from readers can also be found in Series VII: Correspondence.

Arrangement

The material in this series is organized by the title to which it relates, and then typically chronologically within each subseries.

Subseries A: La Reconstruction du Parti Socialiste (1976)
Subseries B: Socialism in Provence, 1871-1914 (1979)
Subseries C: Marxism and the French Left (1986)
Subseries D: Resistance and Revolution in Mediterranean Europe, 1939-1948 (1989)
Subseries E: Past imperfect: French intellectuals, 1944-1956 (1992)
Subseries F: A Grand Illusion? An Essay on Europe (1996)
Subseries G: Burden of Responsibility (1998)
Subseries H: The Politics of Retribution in Europe: World War II and Its Aftermath (2000)
Subseries I: Postwar (2005)
Subseries J: Reappraisals (2008)
Subseries K: Thinking the Twentieth Century (2012)
Subseries L: Ill Fares the Land (2010)
Subseries M: The Memory Chalet (2010)

Subseries I: Postwar (2005)

langmaterial

English

Arrangement

This subseries is further divided to reflect Judt's writing process. His research and notes from Postwar appear in the collection in several groupings that were brought together during processing. These include sets of notes organized by an outline system, as well as by chapter and subject. The way Judt organized his notes is not necessarily reflected in the published version of the book.

Sub-subseries i: Outline Notes
Sub-subseries ii: Subject Notes
Sub-subseries iii: Chapter Notes
Sub-subseries iv: Other Notes and Drafts
Sub-subseries v: Master Set 1st Madeup - Author's Galleys
Sub-subseries vi: Author's correx to final pass
Sub-subseries vii: "Setting MS" manuscript
Sub-subseries viii: Press, reviews, correspondence

Series II: Articles/Essays

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series is comprised primarily of the notes, research, drafts and correspondence related to articles and essays published in a variety of outlets. While this series is extensive in the number of Judt's articles it covers, for some of these works, only photocopies can be found in the collection.

The following abbreviations are used to denote publication titles:
FT - Financial Times
LRB - London Review of Books
NYR - New York Review of Books
NYT - New York Times
TLS - Times Literary Supplement
TNR - The New Republic

Arrangement

This series is divided into two subseries. Reprints of Judt's articles have been separated from his notes and other source material for articles. The articles are arranged chronologically by publication year.

Processing Information

All efforts were made to associate all of Judt's notes to a piece of work, as many were unfiled or filed in vaguely titled folders.

Series III: Subject Files

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series contains research files that did not appear to be connected to any of Judt's specific works. Many of the folder titles are Judt's, but some material was loose or unlabeled and so new folder titles were created. These files contain annotated clippings, printouts and photocopies of articles. There are also annotated typescripts and other loose documents not written by Judt.

Series IV: Teaching Files

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series is separated into two subseries.

Subseries A: Class Material contains syllabi, readings and reading lists, and lecture notes from throughout Judt's teaching career. This material was culled from all over the collection.

Subseries B: Student Files was a pre-existing grouping of files, so original order was maintained here and placed in Series IV: Teaching Files.

Subseries A: Class Material

langmaterial

English

Processing Note

This series contained photocopies of readings for classes Judt taught. Readings not annotated by Judt were discarded and their bibliographic information is included below with reference to the folder they were originally filed in.

Series V: Lectures/Conferences/Addresses

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series contains material related to Judt's speaking engagements outside of his teaching duties, including notes, outlines and drafts as well as research material. In most cases, the folder contents were clear from their titles. Elsewhere, folder titles were created according to the title of the lecture of where the speech was given.

Arrangement

The material in this series is arranged chronologically.

Series VII: Correspondence

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series is separated into two subseries.

Subseries A: Chronological, Misc. contains correspondence from throughout the collection. There was some pre-existing order to the material, but much of it was scattered and brought together into one series.

Subseries B: By Correspondent was a pre-existing grouping of files, titled "Colleagues." Original order was maintained here and the material was placed within this series.

Arrangement

Subseries A is organized alphabetically by given and created folder titles.

Subseries B is organized alphabetically by correspondent.

langmaterial

English

Scope and Contents

This series was pulled together from different parts of the collection, mostly from the Remarque Institute administrative files. Material includes floppy disks of Judt's work, recordings of Remarque Institute Lectures, and assorted CDs and DVDs sent to Judt.

Conditions Governing Access

The University Archives cannot currently provide access to the material in this series. Please contact the Archives for further information.
